            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="faq-container">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What is the best time to take protein supplements?</h3>
                    <p>The best time to take protein supplements depends on your individual goals. For muscle repair and growth, it is often recommended post-workout. However, they can also be taken throughout the day to meet your daily protein needs, especially if you struggle to consume enough protein through food alone.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Are BCAAs necessary if I consume enough protein?</h3>
                    <p>BCAAs can still be beneficial even if your protein intake is sufficient. They help with muscle recovery and reduce fatigue, which can enhance overall performance. BCAAs are particularly useful for individuals engaging in high-intensity or endurance training.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Can I take multiple supplements together?</h3>
                    <p>Yes, many supplements can be taken together, but it is important to consider their interactions and consult with a healthcare professional to ensure proper dosing and effectiveness. Some supplements may interact with medications, so professional advice is crucial.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How do I choose the right multivitamin supplement?</h3>
                    <p>Choosing the right multivitamin involves considering your specific nutritional needs. Look for a product that contains a balanced profile of vitamins and minerals, and avoid those with excessive amounts of any single nutrient. Consulting with a healthcare provider can help you select a supplement that meets your individual health requirements.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What are the benefits of omega-3 fatty acids?</h3>
                    <p>Omega-3 fatty acids, particularly DHA and EPA, are essential for brain health, heart health, and reducing inflammation. They are found in fatty fish and some plant sources. Omega-3s can help improve cognitive function, support cardiovascular health, and reduce the risk of chronic diseases.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Are there any side effects of taking creatine?</h3>
                    <p>Creatine is generally safe for most people when taken in recommended doses. However, some individuals may experience side effects such as weight gain, bloating, or gastrointestinal discomfort. Long-term use at high doses may also affect kidney function, so it is important to follow dosage guidelines and consult with a healthcare provider if you have any concerns.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
